      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: resolve managed SecretRef provider auth",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #92097.\n\nThis teaches provider auth resolution to bridge managed/non-env SecretRef provider `apiKey` entries through the active runtime config snapshot. The source config can keep the managed SecretRef marker/object, while runtime auth uses the already-resolved literal key from the matching runtime snapshot.\n\nThe change is intentionally narrow:\n\n- only applies when the source provider entry has a managed non-env SecretRef marker/object\n- only trusts a runtime snapshot when it matches the active source snapshot\n- does not make marker-only source config work without a runtime snapshot\n- keeps explicit provider api-key config ahead of ambient profile/env auth\n- blocks plugin synthetic local auth from shadowing an explicit managed provider SecretRef\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --write src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test src/agents/model-auth.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose` — 64 passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` — clean, overall patch correct\n- `git diff --check -- src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.test.ts`\n- `pnpm changed:lanes --json` — core and coreTests only\n\nLive E2E/proof from Crabbox on this branch before the final synthetic-shadowing regression hardening:\n\n- provider: `aws`\n- lease: `cbx_4b1a7511118d`\n- run: `run_57dd3b102653`\n- positive SecretRef-backed custom provider reached fake upstream with Authorization present\n- marker-only source config failed before upstream auth, preserving the intended invalid-config behavior\n\nKnown proof gap: `pnpm check:changed` delegated to Blacksmith Testbox but remained queued; I stopped our queued run `tbx_01ktvv2bwe5y5psshpae92fj2w` rather than leaving it pending.\n",
        "branch": "fix/92097-managed-secretref-runtime-auth",
